uk.ac.open.kmi.iserve.discovery.api

Interface Matcher

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ConceptMatcher, DataflowMatcher
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractMatcher, OperationDataflowMatcher, SparqlIndexedLogicConceptMatcher, SparqlLogicConceptMatcher

    public interface Matcher
extends Serializable
    The interface Matcher defines the basic methods to perform a match between two elements.
    Author:
    Carlos Pedrinaci (KMi - The Open University), Pablo Rodriguez Mier (CITIUS - Universidad de Santiago de Compostela)

                  URI destination)
        Perform a match between two URIs (from origin to destination) and returns the result.

        destination - URI of the element to match against
        Returns:

      • match

        com.google.common.collect.Table<URI,URI,MatchResult> match(Set<URI> origins,
                                                           Set<URI> destinations)
        Perform a match between two Sets of URIs (from origin to destination) and returns the result.
        Parameters:
        origins - Set of URIs of the elements to match
        destinations - Set of URIs of the elements to match against
        Returns:
        a Table with the result of the matching indexed by origin URI and then destination URI.

      • listMatchesOfType

        Map<URI,MatchResult> listMatchesOfType(URI origin,
                                       MatchType type)
        Obtains all the matching resources that have a precise MatchType with the URI of origin.
        Parameters:
        origin - URI to match
        type - the MatchType we want to obtain
        Returns:
        a Map containing indexed by the URI of the matching resource and containing the particular MatchResult. If no result is found the Map should be empty not null.
